#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.116"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.116:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.116:0.2"
msgid "12. Dhammakathikavagga"
msgstr "12. A Dhamma speaker"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 116. Dutiyadhammakathikasutta → kathika 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.116:0.3"
msgid "116. Dutiyadhammakathikasutta"
msgstr "116. A Dhamma speaker (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.116:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.3"
msgid "“‘dhammakathiko, dhammakathiko’ti, bhante, vuccati;"
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of a ‘Dhamma speaker’."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.4"
msgid "kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, dhammakathiko hoti;"
msgstr "How is a Dhamma speaker defined?"

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.5"
msgid ""
"kittāvatā dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti, kittāvatā diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto "
"hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How is a mendicant who practices in line with the teaching defined? And how "
"is a mendicant who has attained extinguishment in this very life defined?”"

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.6"
msgid ""
"“Rūpassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘"
"dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, if a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment with form, for "
"its fading away and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant "
"who speaks on Dhamma’."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.7"
msgid ""
"Rūpassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘"
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they practice for disillusionment with form, for its fading away and "
"cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line "
"with the teaching’."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.8"
msgid ""
"Rūpassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘"
"diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment with form, by its fading "
"away and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who has "
"attained extinguishment in this very life’."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.9"
msgid "Vedanāya ce, bhikkhu … pe …"
msgstr "If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment with feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.10"
msgid "saññāya ce, bhikkhu …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.11"
msgid "saṅkhārānañce, bhikkhu …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.12"
msgid ""
"viññāṇassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘"
"dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"consciousness, for its fading away and cessation, they’re qualified to be "
"called a ‘mendicant who speaks on Dhamma’."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.13"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘"
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"If they practice for disillusionment with consciousness, for its fading away "
"and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in "
"line with the teaching’."

msgctxt "sn22.116:1.14"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘"
"diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment with consciousness, by "
"its fading away and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant "
"who has attained extinguishment in this very life’.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.116:1.15"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
